dataset.title: MCR LTER: Coral Reef: Ocean Currents and Biogeochemistry: Moored Thermistor String Data - CBYTS

abstract.para: A vertically moored thermistor string sampled year-round on the reef at Cook's Bay in Moorea, French Polynesia. Sampling began in 2005 and ended in August 2011. All data have been interpolated onto a 20 min grid. Thermistors were spaced vertically along the mooring line 4, 8, 12, 16, and 20 meters above the bottom. Pressure measurements are also provided from two of the instruments typically located at 4 and 20 meters above the bottom.

Furthermore, the user assumes all responsibility for errors in analysis or judgment resulting from use of the data.

geographicCoverage.geographicDescription: Moorea, French Polynesia, CBYTS in Cooks Bay

description.para: This is an ongoing dataset. Data are added twice per year. There is a delay between collection of raw data and the analysis. Public release is not delayed after data is processed.

changeHistory.comment: Per Keith Seydel we've been informed this time series was terminated in August 2011. No further data updates will be apended to this dataset.

protocol.title: Mooring Time Series Protocol - Cooks Bay Thermistor String

section.title: Data Handling:
section.para: Data are filtered and processed to derive calculated data products and for quality control. Raw data are recorded at a short time interval, then processed to remove noise and resampled at 3 points per hour.

protocol.title: Mooring Time Series Protocol - Matlab Data Processing

section.title: Quality Assurance for aggregate completeness
section.para: Data coverage fraction is between 0 and 1 and is defined as the number of measurements actually available divided by the number of measurements theoretically possible in the time aggregation bin.
